This paper deals with an online problem involving the movement of servers to serve requests efficiently, which suggests that it belongs to the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves minimizing costs, which is a common theme in optimization algorithms (cs.AL). The paper also involves game theory, as it considers the competitive ratio of online algorithms (cs.GT). The use of algorithms to efficiently serve requests suggests that it may also belong to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the problem involves mobile servers, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
